From b6a23a3716f835c5e7065f22ddd9bd67a85dc7c5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:40:14 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 03/17] Close two knowledge-channel leaks a live Condition A
 run exposed

Neither was visible from the config or from CORAL.md. Both were found by the
integrity audit on the first real ablation run, not by inspection.

1. Worktree symlinks. setup_shared_state linked every _SHARED_STATE_ITEMS entry
   unconditionally. With knowledge off the targets do not exist, so
   .claude/notes and .claude/skills became *dangling* symlinks: `ls .claude/`
   still showed the agent a notes and a skills directory the ablation had
   deleted. The grader link two lines below was already guarded on existence
   for exactly this reason. Now takes `knowledge` and skips the four dirs.

2. The restart prompt. _build_score_prompt is injected on every agent respawn --
   a second channel into the agent, entirely separate from CORAL.md -- and it
   told Condition A agents to "Check what other agents have tried via
   `coral log -n 10`, `coral notes`, and `coral skills`" and to "Consolidate
   scattered notes, distill reusable skills". Now knowledge-aware, falling back
   to `coral log` / `coral show --diff` and dropping the organize bullet.

KNOWLEDGE_SUBDIRS moves to coral/config.py so project.py (which creates the
dirs) and worktree.py (which links them) cannot drift apart.

Two regression tests, both parametrised over the flag. 15 ablation tests pass,
plus config/hub/islands/workspace/manager/worktree; the byte-identity control
test still holds.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
